# Azure Deployment Guide

## Frontend
Create an Azure Static Web App connected to GitHub.

- App location: `/frontend`
- Output location: `dist`
- Build command: `npm run build`
- Repository variable: `VITE_API_URL=https://YOUR-API.azurewebsites.net`

## Backend
Create a separate Linux App Service using Node.js 22 LTS. Configure:

- `NODE_ENV=production`
- `DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:5432/bmznetwork?sslmode=require`
- `SESSION_SECRET=<long random value>`
- `FRONTEND_URL=https://YOUR-SITE.azurestaticapps.net`
- `TRUST_PROXY=1`
- `SCM_DO_BUILD_DURING_DEPLOYMENT=true`

The API health endpoint is `/api/health`.
